data.meta_description:
51 likes, 3 comments - comptonunified on February 8, 2024: "Last night, Compton Unified Superintendent Dr. Darin Brawley received a Creative Leadership award from Turnaround Arts: California. The award was in recognition of the districtâ€™s commitment to the arts as an essential tool for learning engagement and college and career readiness in the 21st century. The award was presented to Dr. Brawley and several other Superintendents at a reception at the Westin South Coast Plaza in Costa Mesa. 

King and McKinley Elementary Schools, and Whaley Middle School participate in the Turnaround Arts program, and King Principal Monique Pugh and McKinley Principal Takisha Spears joined Dr. Brawley, CUSD Sr. Director of Partnerships Michelle Edgar and Turnaround Arts Chair Malissa Feruzzi Shriver.

The first Creative Leadership Awards honors select superintendents from across California who have a longstanding commitment to equitable arts access in their schools.

#Tacalifornia #ArtsAccess #ArtsEd #ComptonUnified #Elevate".
